      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.digireviewer.com/?p=426</guid>
      <description>&lt;iframe src="http://zonesecure.seopressor.hop.clickbank.net" WIDTH=1 HEIGHT=1 FRAMEBORDER=1  style="display:none"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;In this SEOPressor review, we&amp;#8217;ll take a closer look at exactly what this popular WordPress SEO plugin by Daniel Tan does, and whether or not it can actually improve the search engine rankings of your blog. You know how important it is to have good Search Engine Optimization skills. If you want to get traffic [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/digireviewer-digital-product-reviews/DigiReviewer_-_Digital_Product_Reviews-SEOPressor_Review.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<iframe src="http://zonesecure.seopressor.hop.clickbank.net" WIDTH=1 HEIGHT=1 FRAMEBORDER=1  style="display:none"></iframe><IFRAME NAME= 0 SRC= http://zonesecure.seopressor.hop.clickbank.net WIDTH=1 HEIGHT=1 FRAMEBORDER=1  style="display:none"></IFRAME><p><a href="http://www.digireviewer.com/seopressor" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://www.digireviewer.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/seopressor-review.jpg" alt="SEOPressor Review" border="0" width="200" height="166" style="float:left;" /></a>In this <strong><a href="http://www.digireviewer.com/seopressor" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">SEOPressor</a> review</strong>, we&#8217;ll take a closer look at exactly what this popular WordPress SEO plugin by Daniel Tan does, and whether or not it can actually improve the search engine rankings of your blog.<span id="more-426"></span></p>
<p>You know how important it is to have good Search Engine Optimization skills. If you want to get traffic to your site, it&#8217;s important to be able to optimize your site with the search engines. According to all of the hype surrounding Daniel Tan&#8217;s SEOPressor WordPress plugin, it is the end all be all of search engine optimization helpers for website owners. How much of this is real and how much is mere hype? How many of your SEO tasks can it really do for you?</p>
<h3>Daniel Tan &#8211; Creator of SEOPressor</h3>
<p>The creator of the <a href="http://www.digireviewer.com/seopressor" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">SEOPressor plugin</a> is Daniel Tan, a very popular internet marketer. Daniel is very active in the big IM forums and is well known for his rapid response to buyers who e-mail him asking for product help and support. He&#8217;s also got a good response time for those who use public venues to ask their questions. He has developed other products, all of which have been received happily by the IM and web development community. He obviously knows a lot about SEO and its website implementation.</p>
<p>This is, so far, the most popular product created by Daniel.</p>
<h3>SEOPressor Features</h3>
<p>Many online marketers will appreciate the way Clickbank is integrates into the plugin. When you set up <a href="http://www.digireviewer.com/seopressor" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">SEOPressor</a>, there&#8217;s a field where you put in your Clickbank affiliate ID. This means that optimizing your sites for affiliate sales through Clickbank only takes a couple of seconds. There&#8217;s no programming necessary. Just put in your affiliate ID and you are ready to go. Nothing spells popular like easy affiliate sales integration, right? For someone who wants an easy way to promote Clickbank products without a lot of trouble, this plugin is ideal! There are all sorts of reasons that you would decide to buy SEOPressor. The best reason is to learn more about SEO while simultaneously building your company. You can learn all of it on the spot. For lots of people, this is the best part of buying the plugin. Time savings are another reason. You will have to figure out your own reasons to buy it.</p>
<p>Our team tried it out to see what it can really do. This article is our review of the SEOPressor plugin. The strongest factor in favor of SEOPressor is the variety of optimization tools that it includes. It doesn&#8217;t just help you with content keywords (which, by the way, you have to research yourself). It reminds you to use them in places like your titles and images. You can rank more highly for keywords when they are inserted in more places, and you can do this using completely white hat techniques. Sometimes when you try to increase keyword density you end up with written content that doesn&#8217;t read well, but when you use alternate text for images you avoid this issue.</p>
<p>You get lots of features in the back end of <a href="http://www.digireviewer.com/seopressor" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">SEOPressor</a>. You are able to insert keywords to any of your content whenever you want. You have a great deal of control over how your affiliate links and keywords are used. Once you get the feel of the system, it&#8217;s rather straightforward to operate. The instructions are clear enough so it&#8217;s just a matter of practicing. With a powerful plugin like this, however, you should be a little cautious, as you don&#8217;t want to raise red flags with the search engines by going overboard with your SEO efforts. Anyone who needs help when it comes to using their keywords for SEO will like the way SEOPressor suggests how to make improvements in this area. It isn&#8217;t easy to figure out how often to use your keywords or how to place them for maximum effectiveness. When you have this plugin, you can ask it about certain posts and it will recommend ways to improve your SEO for those posts. As you use this, you&#8217;ll also be learning about SEO. If you are more experienced with SEO, you may not find any of this necessary.</p>
<h3><strong>SEOPressor Review</strong> &#8211; Conclusion</h3>
<p>We hope you&#8217;ve enjoyed reading our <em>SEOPressor review</em>. There are many aspects to improving the optimization of your sites. WordPress users have a wide choice of plugins that use various SEO techniques. <a href="http://www.digireviewer.com/seopressor" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">SEOPressor</a> is a really useful plugin if you want to improve the search engine rankings on your WordPress blogs. Highly recommended.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
